             Paraguay beat Slovakia 2-0 to move
atop Group F at soccerâ€™s World Cup today in Bloemfontein, South
Africa.  
 Enrique Vera scored the opener in the 27th minute,
finishing with the outside of his right boot after collecting a
pass from Lucas Barrios. Cristian Riveros finished with a first
time shot after 86 minutes.  
 Paraguay has four points from two games, with Slovakia,
defending champion Italy and New Zealand all on one point. Italy
and New Zealand play their second game in Nelspruit later today.  
          
          


  


        